-- Ivory Coast, Zambia Advance to African Cup Of Nations Semifinals
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-02-04T21:12:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/ivory-coast-zambia-advance-to-african-cup-of-nations-semifinals.html
Ivory Coast  and Zambia both won 3-0
to advance to the semifinals of soccer’s African Cup of Nations.  Didier Drogba  scored two goals and Yaya Toure added one as
Ivory Coast beat tournament co-host  Equatorial Guinea . Drogba
also had a first-half penalty kicked saved by goalkeeper Danilo.  Stoppila Sunzu, Christopher Katongo and James Chamanga had
the goals as Zambia beat 10-man  Sudan  to move into the final
four for the first time in 16 years. Zambia scored twice after
Sudan’s Saif Eldin was sent off in the 65th minute for a second
yellow card.  Ivory Coast next plays the winner of tomorrow’s
quarterfinal between co-host Gabon and  Mali , while Sudan will
face either Ghana or  Tunisia . The semifinals will be played Feb.
8, with the final four days later.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
